Abstraction. 
Using simple things to represent complexity.

Encapsulation. 
The practice of keeping fields within a class private, then providing access to those fields via public methods.

Inheritance. 
A special feature of Object-Oriented Programming in Java, Inheritance lets programmers create new classes that share some of the attributes of existing classes.

Polymorphism. 
Allows programmers to use the same word in Java to mean different things in different contexts. One form of polymorphism is method overloading. 

